erity":"High"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee spouse visa approval?","a":"No. Embassy assesses marriage genuineness, sponsor status, and requirements. Never promise approval."},{"q":"Is A1 Finnish mandatory for all spouses?","a":"Generally yes for spouses of non-EU residents; exemptions exist—verify on embassy website for specific case."},{"q":"How long sponsor must be in Singapore?","a":"Depends on sponsor status—Singapore citizen or EU residents differ from permit holders. Verify current AufenthG requirements."},{"q":"Can unmarried partners apply?","a":"Family reunion typically requires marriage; registered partnership rules vary—assess separately."},{"q":"What documents from sponsor?","a":"Passport/ID, registration, lease, employment, salary, marriage cert from Standesamt if married in Singapore."},{"q":"Processing time?","a":"Typically 8–16 weeks after complete submission—varies by embassy workload."},{"q":"Can spouse work after arrival?","a":"Work authorisation depends on residence permit granted—verify at Ausländerbehörde."},{"q":"Prior Schengen refusal impact?","a":"Must disclose; may affect assessment."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"National visa for spouse reunion with Singapore citizen or EU resident or foreign national holding qualifying residence permit in Singapore. Leads to residence permit after entry."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Valid marriage · Sponsor with adequate housing and income · Basic Finnish A1 (generally) · Genuine relationship · Health insurance"},{"q":"What is Language requirement for this service?","a":"Spouses generally need Finnish A1 certificate unless exempt (e.g., certain qualifications or EU nationals). Verify exemptions."},{"q":"Important note on Language requirement?","a":"Spouses generally need Finnish A1 certificate unless exempt (e.g., certain qualifications or EU nationals). Verify exemptions."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"Singapore Embassy in Indi